<br>
-Anabollic posts, and says that someone called him at 4am.<br>
-Anabollic is a lying scammer. Anabollic doesn't even post as himself, he posts a story about how he's someone else, you have got the wrong guy.<br>
-Anabollic lied throughout this post, but you take that one pearl of truth and champion Anabollic's &quot;please don't call and harass me&quot; plea.<br>
-Anabollic scammed, stole, and rubbed it in; relished in it.<br>
<br>
Let's hit that last point again, yes-yes? <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Anabollic relished in the pain and misfortune he caused other people.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> And then tells you that someone called him at 4am. And you believed him. Do you see where I'm going with this?<br>
<br>
Now secondly: For all you folks he keep harping about how he's a poor minor. He's a Junior in Highschool. I was 18 when I was a Senior, so he's probably not that far from not being a minor in any case. That's not my main point, however.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm just a youngin' myself, at 20, but I'm sick and fucking tired of you guys saying that the poor minor deserves to be spanked but not harrassed. Maybe you don't realize this, but by the time you're a Junior in highschool, you're not a kid anymore. You're making decisions about the future, you probably have a job, you probably curse and might smoke or drink, you've probably lost your virginity by now, and you sure as hell are old enough to take responsibility for your actions.<br>
<br>
There is no fucking excuse for a Junior in High School to behave like he did. None. I don't care if he's not quite legal, yet, its not like something magical happens that transforms him when he hits that magic number. Nope, the only difference is that all that porn he's been looking at is now legal, and its a lot easier for him to buy cigarettes.<br>
<br>
So quit kidding yourself by thinking he's just a little kid who can't take responsibility for what he did. He's a Junior in High School, not a 14 year old in Junior High. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=703956" target="top">Duergin MacLeod</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, Shaman of 51 Spirits... who's staying that away until he's got his Epic</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zekspawn>Zekspawn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/2/03 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=55.topic&index=87>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Much Needed Clarification (Anabollic Haters Read)</span><hr size=1> How do you propose SoE police every person's activity in the game?  Someone posting on a message board isn't an admission...how do you know for sure that it wasn't someone who got scammed pretending to be him to get more people mad at this person?<br>
