<br>
In California the knowledge of the recording, before the recording is made, is consent and makes it admissible. In an older case, the simple fact that an answering machine picked up the line before the person did was sufficient for &quot;knowledge&quot; of the recording, and thus consent for the recording to be made, so the recorded conversation was admissible in court.<br>
<br>
Xethux<br>
